@NODE inst "MUIXAnim - English manual"
@{B}*** Installing MUI XAnim ***@{UB}

Here are the following requirements:

   - Operating System 2.04 (37.175) or higher

   - 68020 CPU or higher 

   - AGA or GFX Board recommended

   - MUI 2.3 or better  (© Stefan Stuntz) @{i}Available on Aminet...@{ui}

   - XAnim (© Mark Podlipec) @{i}Available on Aminet...@{ui}


The easiest way to install MUI XAnim is to use the installer script 
supplied in this archive.
@ENDNODE




@NODE use "MUIXAnim - English manual"
@{B}*** Usage of MUIXAnim***@{UB}

@{fg shine}
@{B}@{i}*** Main Menu: ***@{UB}@{ui}
@{fg text}

@{B}Play Anim:@{UB}
   Just view the animation when all options have been selected.

@{B}Help:@{UB}
   The Help guide you are watching at this time.

@{B}About:@{UB}
   About the application

@{B}Save Config:@{UB}
   This is very usefull when you always use same options.
   Config file is stored in ENV: and ENVArc: and automatically loaded
   when you start MUI XAnim

@{B}Quit:@{UB}
   Quit the program.

@{fg shine}
@{B}Select XAnim Path:@{UB}
@{fg text}

@{i}   (optional)@{ui}
   Here you can select where your XAnim program is stored (if it is not in
   the same directory).

   Example: you have stored xanim in @{i}Work:Xanim/@{ui}
            you should enter:  @{i}Work:XAnim/XAnim@{ui}

   If you don't specify something, the program consider that XAnim is
   in the same directory as MUIXAnim.

@{fg shine}
@{B}Select Anim File:@{UB}
@{fg text}
   Here you choose the name of the anim you want to see.

@{fg shine}   
@{B}Info:@{UB}
@{fg text}
   Gives some help about gadgets.


   

@{fg shine}
@{B}@{i}*** Group Options : ***@{UB}@{ui}
@{fg text}
   In this group are all options included in MUI XAnim.
   For further details about the options, have a look in xanim.readme. 


@{fg shine}@{u}Audio Options@{uu}@{fg text}
 	
@{B}Audio disabled:@{UB}
   If this is on, you'll not be able to listen to the sound that
   comes with some anims file (Ex:QuickTime,AVI...)
   Note that when turned on, anim playback may be very slow.

@{B}Sync Frame/Sound:@{UB}
   If on, XAnim will skip video frames in order to help keeping
   video in sync with audio.
   
@{B}Change Volume:@{UB}
    If on,Use Set Volume Value.
    If off,Use Default Value (40).

@{B}Set Volume:@{UB}
   (only available when change volume is turned on)
   Sets the initial audio volume (0=Lowest,100=Highest,40=Default)



@{fg shine}@{u}Color Options@{uu}@{fg text}

@{B}True Color dither:@{UB}
   This option samples the color of true color animations ahead of time
   and forms a color lookup table.

@{B}Default cmap:@{UB}
   Allocates color from the X11 Display's default cmap.

@{B}Grey Scale@{UB}
   Converts True color anim to grey.



@{fg shine}@{u}Misc Options@{uu}@{fg text}

@{B}Buffering@{UB}
   Uncompress and buffer image before displaying.
   (Could take some time and need a lot of memory)

@{B}Direct from Disk@{UB}
   Don't load anim in memory but read each section only when needed

@{B}Scale Anim@{UB}
   Scale the size of the animation.

@{B}Scale Factor@{UB}
   Enter the value of the scaling (enter a fnum only).
   Example : You want to halve your anim -> factor = 0.5



@{fg shine}@{u}Env Variables@{uu}@{fg text}  

@{B}Askmode Requester@{UB}
   Opens a requester to choose resolution and depth.

@{B}Debug@{UB}
   Gives various informations about the animation file.

@{B}Usepubscreen Workbench@{UB}
   Uses Workbench screen instead of XAnim's one.

@{B}GFX Card@{UB}
   Uses WritePixelArray instead of Chunky.


@{i}@{u}For more informations about options, have a look in @{ui}@{B}"XAnim.readme"@{uu}@{UB}
@ENDNODE


@NODE compat "MUIXAnim - English manual"
@{B}*** Compatibilities ***@{UB}

@{B} MUIXAnim has been tested without any problems on folowing configurations:@{UB}

	- A1200 Microbotics M1230/50MHz/16Mb Fast RAM/68882 50MHz
                Kickstart 40.68 (3.1) Workbench 40.42
	        Picasso II (2Mb) GFX Board

	- A1200 68EC020 14MHz/No Fast RAM
	        Kickstart 39.106 (3.0) Workbench 39.9

	- A2000 GVP 68030/25 MHz/4Mb Fast RAM/68882 25MHz

@ENDNODE

